  "prompt": "What kind of teachers do you like best?",
  "response": "The kind of teachers I like best are those who are **passionate**, **understanding**, and **engaging**. Here\u2019s what makes them stand out:\n\n1. **Passionate about their subject**: Teachers who genuinely love what they teach inspire curiosity and enthusiasm in their students. Their energy is contagious!\n\n2. **Supportive and empathetic**: They care about their students\u2019 well-being, not just their academic performance. They\u2019re patient and willing to help when someone struggles.\n\n3. **Interactive and creative**: They make learning fun and meaningful by using innovative methods, like hands-on activities, discussions, or real-world examples.\n\n4. **Encouraging and motivating**: They believe in their students\u2019 potential and push them to grow while providing constructive feedback.\n\n5. **Approachable and open-minded**: They create a safe space where students feel comfortable asking questions, sharing ideas, or making mistakes.\n\nUltimately, the best teachers are those who make learning a positive and impactful experience. \ud83d\ude0a What kind of teachers do *you* appreciate?",
